The State of the Nation Address is usually a glitzy affair. But, in the light of a struggling economy, Parliament has decided to tone down the event. Speaker, Thandi Modise, says even the gala dinner will be no more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some opposition parties have threatened to disrupt the 2020 State of the Nation Address (Sona). President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver his fourth Sona in Parliament on Thursday. READ: Sona 2020 road closures National Assembly Speaker Thandi Modise says should there be any disruption, the rules will be applied. "So we will be applying the rules."